    "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nI expect `pyright` to stop and start again after passing in the command `:LspRestart`, but `pyright` remains in a stopped state after it has stopped. I have to run `:LspStart` to get it to start again.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.9.1\r\n\r\n### Nvim-lspconfig version\r\n\r\nLatest\r\n\r\n### Operating system and version\r\n\r\nmacOS Ventura\r\n\r\n### Affected language servers\r\n\r\n`pyright`\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. `:LspRestart`\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n`pyright` stops, but does not start back up. I waited for a few minutes.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Minimal config\r\n\r\n```Lua\r\nI used astronvim, but it should be reproduceable with vanilla config too.\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### LSP log\r\n\r\nN/A",
